Field.name: param3
Field.description:
the third parameters of the command.
 this is used by commands which are unsupported yet. parameter is defined to support hw - hw will write
 the parameter here, and pcode is the one that will disqualified the command with "illegal" cc.

Field.name: param2
Field.description:
the second parameters of the command.
 in case of read_pcs/write_pcs command, this would be the parameter for the specific pcs index (sliceid/pp/...).
 in case of rdiacoremsr, this would be the msr id.
 the content is kept for peci use until run_busy is cleared.

Field.name: param1
Field.description:
the first parameter of the command.
 in case of a read_pcs/write_pcs command, this would be the pcs index.
 in case of rdiacoremsr, this would be the threadid/sa/...
the content is kept for peci use until run_busy is cleared.
